    <text>
        <body>
            
            <!-- Begins with the text of the petition. -->
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="cww.01056.001.jpg"/>
            
            <div1 type="petition" subtype="handwritten" corresp="#rg21">

                <div2 type="document" subtype="handwritten">
                    <opener>
                        <salute>To John A Smith <choice><abbr>Esqr</abbr><expan>Esquire</expan></choice>. Clerk of the Circuit Court of the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName></salute>
                        <salute>Sir</salute>
                    </opener>
                    
                    <p>Mr <persName>John F. Boone</persName> having claim to the labor or service of <persName><hi rend="underline">Mary Thomas</hi></persName> aged 45 years &#38; her daughter <persName><hi rend="underline">Mary Catharine</hi> Thomas</persName> and having neglected to file his schedule as provided by the act of Congress concerning Emancipation approved <date when="1862-04-16">April 16, 1862</date>, this Petitioner files her Petition for herself &#38; daughter <persName>Mary Catharine Thomas</persName> in lieu thereof according to the provisions of an act of Congress amendatory thereto approved <date when="1862-07-12">July 12 1862</date>. Petitioner shows that she &#38; her child had resided in this <placeName>District</placeName> ever since she was a child &#38; was in said <placeName>District</placeName> &#38; has remained till the present time by the consent of her owner said <persName>Boone</persName>
                    <table>
                        <row>
                            <cell></cell>
                            <cell>Age</cell>
                            <cell>Color</cell>
                            <cell></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><persName>Mary Thomas</persName></cell>
                            <cell>40</cell>
                            <cell>Dark Brown</cell>
                            <cell><unclear reason="illegible" cert="high" resp="#jc">5 ft 6 inches</unclear></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><persName>Mary Catharine</persName></cell>
                            <cell>4 &#189;</cell>
                            <cell>dark <choice><abbr>do</abbr><expan>ditto</expan></choice></cell>
                            <cell>3 feet high</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                    </p>
                    
                    <closer>
                        <signed>her X mark <persName>Mary Thomas</persName></signed><lb/>
                        In presence of
                        <signed><persName>Geo E H Day</persName></signed>
                    </closer>             
                </div2>                        
                                        
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="cww.01056.002.jpg"/>
                
                <div2 type="cover" subtype="handwritten">
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>paid</ab>
                        <ab><persName>Jno F Boone</persName> schedule</ab>
                        <ab><persName>Mary Thomas</persName></ab>
                        <ab><persName>Mary C Thomas</persName></ab>
                    </div3>
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>Recorded in Manumission Record no. 2 folio 60</ab>
                    </div3>
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>Filed <date when="1862-07-26">July 26th 1862</date></ab>                      
                    </div3>
                                       
                    <div3 type="section">                        
                        <p>The Commissioners satisfied on the testimony of <persName>Martha L Shoemaker</persName> and <persName>Basil Jackson</persName> of the truth of within statement, order the same to be so reported to the Clerk of the Circuit Court of the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName>.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><persName>Wm. R. Woodward</persName><lb/>
                                Clerk</signed>
                            <dateline><date when="1862-07-26">July 26 1862</date></dateline>
                        </closer>
                    </div3>                    
                </div2>
            </div1>
            
            <!-- Evidence pertaining to the case begins here. -->
           
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="cww.01056.003.jpg"/>
            <div1 type="evidence" corresp="#rg217" subtype="handwritten">
                <dateline><date when="1862-07-29">July 26, 1862</date>.</dateline>
                
                <div2 type="procedural">
                    <ab><persName>Mary Thomas</persName> and<lb/>
                    <persName>Catharine</persName> her daughter</ab>
                    <ab>servant of <persName>John F. Boone</persName></ab>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="testimony">
                    <p><persName>Martha L. Shoemaker</persName>. known <persName>Mary Thomas</persName> ever since I was child. I knew she had a child but never saw it. I have no doubt it is her. She was here prior to and since <date when="1862-04-16">16 April</date> and always lived here. She belonged to <persName>Mrs Boone</persName> when she was <persName>Mrs Edward Dyer</persName>.</p>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="testimony">
                    <p><persName>Basil Jackson</persName> (<choice><abbr>col.</abbr><expan>colored</expan></choice> This is <persName>Marys</persName> child I know her to be. had two children one of them dead</p>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="procedural">
                    <ab>(<choice><abbr>cert</abbr><expan>certificate</expan></choice> ordered)</ab>
                </div2>                
               
                <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="cww.01056.004.jpg"/>
                <div2 type="cover">
                    <ab><persName>Mary Thomas</persName></ab>
                    <ab><persName>Catharine</persName> her daughter</ab>
                    <ab><date when="1862-07-26">July 26</date></ab>
                </div2>
            </div1>            
        </body>
    </text>
